ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A required class on ethic topics in bioresearch.
I would not recommend this course. Unfortunately, it's a requirement and frankly was disruptive to time I could have spent in the lab or writing my thesis.
I would recommend the course, as it provides us with some great questions and things to consider about a life in science.
Pretty typical ethics course. It was fine. The readings were interesting and the conversations were also interesting. I also learned more about the resources available for graduate students.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Answered many questions about grad student life. Otherwise it will be reasonably helpful going forward.
This course added nothing to my knowledge. It didn't contribute anything to my research except taking away time I could have spent working on it.
